The syntax of the Endloop Statement in Actian 4GL OpenROAD is:

endloop [label];

The 'label' parameter is optional and specifies which loop to terminate.

In Actian 4GL OpenROAD, the Endloop Statement can be used with nested loops by specifying a label. For example:

B: while condition1 do
   while condition2 do
      if condition3 then
         endloop B;
      endif;
   endwhile
endwhile;

Here, 'endloop B' terminates both the inner and outer loops when condition3 is true.
